Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
All laboratory values are within normal limits except for a mildly elevated hemoglobin (16.3 g/dL). This could indicate mild hemoconcentration or dehydration but may also be normal for this patient. No evidence of anemia, infection, electrolyte imbalance, or renal dysfunction. Clinical correlation is recommended.
